              "lang": "en-us",
              "slug": "fallacy",
              "first_publication_date": "2019-09-23T07:55:49+0000",
              "last_publication_date": "2019-09-29T06:32:36+0000",
              "link_type": "Document",
              "isBroken": false
            }
          },
          {
            "start": 616,
            "end": 636,
            "type": "em"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Actually, the situation is worse still: if the things being compared are statistically independent, then it takes only fourteen comparisons for it to be more likely than not to get a statistically significant result by chance. This is a result of the multiplication rule of probability theory.",
        "spans": [
          {
            "start": 251,
            "end": 292,
            "type": "em"
          }
        ]
      }
